        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-18 13:31:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nBe consistent in all descriptions of a field, tenant name, in this case, throughout the change, and don't mention non-public internal names of systems (as noted in Alex's comments).  I'd recommend simply saying \"Tenant Name.\"  The commit message should probably also say something about why adding this field is useful.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1094379c5dd484471cf5505062fff08af3b2e965",
