      },
      {
        "id": "fa65b96b804c3641b2f07cf394378b65deed8e19",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1949,
          "name": "Alex Shatov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ashatov@hotmail.com",
          "username": "alex_sh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-06-18 15:01:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n@Shadi - please reformat the commit-message line - it has a limit of 72 chars per line.  The title is up to 50 chars\n\n@Tony -- yes apparently we have the original files from Jack with tabs (4 spaces) and other files with spaces as indents.  That is my fault (default in my text editor was set to spaces - I missed seeing tabs from Jack).  So, every file I created or reformatted, got converted to 4 spaces.  -- I admit that is not consistent between the files and should be fixed eventually one or the other way.  At least if you open those files in gerrit review, the lineup is not messed up.  What we got on deployment-handler.js right now is a mix of tabs and spaces as indents in the same file - that breaks the reading in gerrit review and perhaps other editors - we should keep the tabs/spaces consistent at least per file and eventually move to the consistent format per the whole project.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
